<p>By turning the semantics into puzzle pieces and their interactions.</p>

<p>Here, the alien wants a gold star. You have a gold star but you must use all the components. So, you put the star into the mechanism and it comes out. The basic idea of a function is taught.</p>

<p><img src="/sandbox/img/starboy/starboy5.png" alt="Alt" /></p>

<p><img src="/sandbox/img/starboy/starboy1.png" alt="Alt" /></p>

<p>Starboy (reduct) is a puzzle game that teaches code semantics to children.</p>

<p>I did game design and narrative. We submitted and were accepted to CHI EA â€˜17:</p>

<p><img src="/sandbox/img/starboy/chi.png" alt="Alt" /></p>

<p>https://dl.acm.org/doi/abs/10.1145/3027063.3048415</p>

<p>Hereâ€™s the story: Starboy (transparent stand in for the little prince) crashes on various planets. To fuel his ship he has to help aliens get what they want.</p>

